Package: countSFA
Type: Package
Title: Count-Data Stochastic Frontier Models
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: person("Samuele", "Centorrino",
                  email = "scentorrino@proton.me",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Maximum likelihood estimation of Poisson stochastic frontier
    models for count outcomes. Supports three parametric families for the
    one-sided inefficiency term: the exponential distribution, with a
    closed-form marginal probability mass function via the lower
    incomplete gamma function; the general Gamma distribution, with a
    marginal PMF expressible as an absolutely convergent alternating
    series and an automatically chosen truncation depth; and the
    half-normal distribution of Fé and Hofler (2013)
    <doi:10.1007/s11123-012-0286-y>, evaluated by maximum simulated
    likelihood with antithetic Halton draws. Provides PMF evaluation,
    MLE fitting with log-scale reparameterisation, posterior technical
    efficiency scores, model comparison utilities (likelihood-ratio and
    Vuong (1989) <doi:10.2307/1912557> tests), and helpers for
    cross-orientation use (production and cost frontiers).
